  "brief": "<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Market Overview</h2>\n\nFutures are catching a bid on peace deal optimism, with QQQ leading at +1.30% and small caps ripping +1.68% as risk-on sentiment dominates. VIX holding stubbornly above 28 suggests traders aren't fully buying this rally yet, while the dollar's getting hammered on intervention chatter and geopolitical developments.\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> What to Watch</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>ADP Employment (12:15 ET)</strong> - Critical read on labor market ahead of Friday's NFP</li>\n<li><strong>MBA Mortgage Data (11:00 ET)</strong> - Housing market pulse with rates still elevated</li>\n<li><strong>Fed Musalem Speech (1:30 ET)</strong> - Hawkish or dovish spin on current policy stance</li>\n<li><strong>Iran Peace Deal Headlines</strong> - Any confirmation or denial will move energy and defense stocks hard</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Sector Rotation</h2>\n\nTech is absolutely ripping at +2.21% with materials close behind at +1.74% as growth trades recover on peace hopes and dollar weakness. Energy's barely budging despite the Hormuz incident - tells you everything about where traders think oil's heading if this deal gets done. Comm services lagging at -0.40% as the only red sector.\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-green\"><div class=\"callout-label\">✦ Bull Case</div>Peace deal eliminates major geopolitical risk premium, unlocks growth trades, and could spark sustained risk-on rotation with small caps already leading the charge.</div>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-amber\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚡ Key Driver</div>Any headline confirmation or denial on the Iran deal will be the primary market mover - watch Reuters and State Department feeds closely.</div>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-red\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚠ Bear Case</div>VIX refusing to crack below 28 despite the rally suggests institutional skepticism - if peace talks stall, this reversal could be violent with small caps most vulnerable.</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Levels That Matter</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>SPY 725</strong> - Key resistance from April highs, break confirms continuation</li>\n<li><strong>QQQ 685</strong> - Next logical target if tech momentum holds through open</li>\n<li><strong>VIX 26.50</strong> - Critical break point for sustained risk-on move</li>\n<li><strong>IWM 285</strong> - Small cap breakout level that confirms broad market participation</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr>\n<p><em>Not a prediction. A preparation. Make your plan before the bell.</em></p>"
